&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Doha, Qatar.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Union Labour &amp;amp; Employment Minister Dr. Mansukh Mandaviya led the Indian delegation to the Second World Summit for Social Development (WSSD-2) held in Doha, Qatar, from 4&amp;ndash;6 November 2025.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Summit focused on global cooperation for poverty eradication, productive employment, and social inclusion.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s delegation, led by Dr. Mandaviya, shared its achievements in lifting 248 million people out of multidimensional poverty between 2011&amp;ndash;2023.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s social protection coverage increased from 19% in 2015 to 64.3% in 2025, benefitting over 940 million citizens.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NITI Aayog hosted a side event titled &amp;ldquo;Pathways Out of Poverty: India&amp;rsquo;s Experience in Empowering the Last Mile&amp;rdquo; during the Summit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World Summit for Social Development (WSSD)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;First held in Copenhagen, Denmark, in 1995.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Key goals: &lt;strong&gt;Poverty eradication, full and productive employment, and social inclusion.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Second WSSD (WSSD-2) in 2025 reaffirmed these commitments through the &lt;strong&gt;Doha Political Declaration.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s Initiatives Showcased&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pradhan Mantri Garib Kalyan Anna Yojana (PMGKAY)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Free foodgrain distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PM Awas Yojana&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Affordable housing for all.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jan Dhan&amp;ndash;Aadhaar&amp;ndash;Mobile (JAM) Trinity&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Direct, transparent benefit delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International Partners&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Participating nations included &lt;strong&gt;Brazil, Maldives, and ILO.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focus on advancing the &lt;strong&gt;2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Institute of Urban Affairs (NIUA).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HUDCO has signed an MoU with the National Institute of Urban Affairs (NIUA) to collaborate on urban infrastructure and sustainable urban development.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The MoU was signed on November 24 to promote programmes related to urban infrastructure, infrastructure investment, and HUDCO&amp;rsquo;s Urban Invest Window (UiWIN).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The partnership also focuses on capacity building through seminars, workshops, conferences, and joint research initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The agreement is non-binding and will remain valid for five years.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The MoU explores collaboration with multilateral funding agencies to support sustainable urban development projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HUDCO (Housing and Urban Development Corporation Ltd.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A government-owned PSU under the Ministry of Housing &amp;amp; Urban Affairs&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Provides financing and consultancy for housing and urban infrastructure projects&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focuses on sustainable and inclusive urban development&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NIUA (National Institute of Urban Affairs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Autonomous research and policy organization under Ministry of Housing &amp;amp; Urban Affairs&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Acts as a think tank for urban policy, planning, and governance&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Conducts research, capacity building, and urban development initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Memorandum of Understanding (MoU)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A formal non-binding agreement outlining collaboration between entities&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Framework for cooperation with project-specific agreements signed later&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Defines objectives, scope, roles, and duration of partnership&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
